  "_note": "Path prefixes containing '*' use glob-aware matching (fnmatch-style). Use '*/docs/dev/foo-' to match the prefix 'docs/dev/foo-' anywhere under any worktree. Use '/docs/dev/foo-' to anchor at any path that ends with '/docs/dev/foo-' boundary. Shared protected list is the SOLE catch-all for /.claude/ — DO NOT add broad '/.claude/' to denied prefixes; use only the explicit subdirs above so legitimate worktree artifact paths remain writable. spec-20260507-142952 AC-1: cp-state-*.json globs are documented here AND propagated into every subagent role's denied_write_path_prefixes; spec-check.py is the only legal writer. policy_version 2 (spec-20260508-221237 cycle 4 manual reorg, 2026-05-09): adds first-class roles timeline and transportation mirroring their .md tools: [Read, Bash, Skill] declaration, with denied_tools=[Write,Edit,MultiEdit,NotebookEdit] as defense-in-depth Feb-13-2026 incident lock. These two role table entries are the ONLY residue of spec-20260508-221237 in the global tool-policy; the ga''ode-maps allowlist enforcement was moved to project-local /root/travel-planner/.claude/policies/gaode_policy.json + hooks/pretool-gaode_policy.py per user directive.",
